attributes.Long form description: The instructor tells the student to open all the  boxes and pull out the base and wheels, checks the air on the wheels and then is told to take the tripods out and put them on the wheels. After that the instructor tells the student to put on the body and the head, then to count the lens caps, put in the batteries, clean the lens and adjust it.

attributes.Transcription: First thing is to open all the boxes.

attributes.Action sentence: The student opens all the NavVis boxes.
The student pulls the base and wheels out of the box.

attributes.Transcription: Should i pull out the base?
Check the air pressure on the wheels.

attributes.Action sentence: The student checks the air in the wheels.

attributes.Transcription: Take out the tripods and put on the wheels.

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the wheels onto the kickstands.
The student mounts the M6 body.

attributes.Transcription: Now, Uh, put on the body, neck.
take out the handbars and put those on place.

attributes.Action sentence: The student mounts the head of the M6.
The student counts and removes the lens caps.
The student inserts the M6 batteries.

attributes.Transcription: This battery hole is having trouble.
Clean the lens cap with a microfiber cloth.

attributes.Action sentence: The student cleans the lens of the m6 head using a microfiber cloth.
The student lifts the head of the M6.
The student turns on the M6 machine.
The student rotates the m6 machine and turns it off.
